Reasoning: The paper describes the application of Neural Network-based Optical Character Recognition (OCR) to scanned images of historical books, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR), deep learning (DL), computer vision (CV), natural language processing (NLP), and human-computer interaction (HCI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.DL (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
